oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Roane College, Wheat, Roane County, TN. (Wikipedia: Wheat was a farming community in Roane County, Tennessee. The area is now in the city of Oak Ridge. ...Poplar Creek Seminary, founded in 1886 by a Presbyterian minister, later became Roane College. In 1908, the college transferred ownership of the building to Wheat High School.)
